  "title": "The BMI-HDEEG dataset 2",
  "description": "A high-density scalp electroencephalogram (EEG) dataset acquired during sensorimotor rhythm-based brain-computer interface (BCI) tasks. This dataset comprises recordings from multiple subjects performing motor imagery and related sensorimotor activities, designed to support the development and validation of BCI systems. The high-density electrode configuration enables detailed spatial characterization of cortical activity underlying motor control and brain-computer communication.",
